{
  "texts": [
    "Liu et al. (2012b) first proposed a solution to the issue of cross-scene fashion retrieval.",
    "An occasion-oriented fashion retrieval approach was also proposed, in which the low-level visual features of clothing and highlevel occasion category features were fused with mid-level clothing attributes.",
    "A feature representation that was able to characterize the clothing appearance well, using a posedependent approach, was used for fashion retrieval (Vittayakorn et al. 2015).",
    "These feature representation schemes can facilitate the quantitative analysis of cross-domain clothing image similarity.",
    "Thanks to their powerful feature extraction capabilities, deep learning methods have become the most common solution to the problem of fashion retrieval."
  ]
}